### API Testing File for VS Code REST Client
### Install "REST Client" extension to use this file
### Shortcut: Ctrl+Shift+D to send request

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api

### ==========================================
### GET REQUESTS
### ==========================================

### Get all items
GET {{baseUrl}}/items

### Get item by ID (change 1 to any ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/items/1

### Get non-existent item (should return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/items/999

### ==========================================
### POST REQUEST - Create new item
### ==========================================

POST {{baseUrl}}/items
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Learn REST APIs",
  "description": "Understand how to build REST APIs with Node.js"
}

### ==========================================
### PUT REQUEST - Complete update
### ==========================================

### Replace entire item with ID 1
PUT {{baseUrl}}/items/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Master Node.js",
  "description": "Become an expert in Node.js backend development",
  "completed": true
}

### ==========================================
### PATCH REQUEST - Partial update
### ==========================================

### Update only the completed status
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/items/2
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "completed": false
}

### Update only the title
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/items/3
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Advanced Concepts"
}

### ==========================================
### DELETE REQUEST
### ==========================================

### Delete item with ID 1
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/items/1

### ==========================================
### Test Health Check
### ==========================================

GET http://localhost:3000
